b'A. Entrance\xc2\xa0Requirements '
b'Graduate Program'
b' The department reviews each applicant on an individual basis. Complete transcripts of all undergraduate and any graduate work must be submitted. In addition to meeting the Graduate College minimum requirements, applicants must meet the following program requirements: Baccalaureate Field:'
b'Engineering or Chemistry.'
b'Grade Point Average:'
b'At least 3.00/4.00 for the final 60 semester hours (90 quarter hours) of undergraduate study, for the master\xe2\x80\x99s program, and at least 3.50 for the doctoral program. In exceptional cases, applicants with averages below 3.00 but above 2.75 may be admitted on limited standing if they show evidence of substantial ability to complete the program successfully.'
b'Tests Required: (ETS institution code: 1851)'
b'GRE general'
b'Minimum English Competency Test Score:'
b'TOEFL 80, with subscores of Reading 19, Listening 17, Speaking 20, and Writing 21 (iBT Internet-based), OR,'
b'IELTS 6.5, with subscores of 6.0 for all four subscores, OR,'
b'PTE-Academic 54, with subscores of Reading 51, Listening 47, Speaking 53, and Writing 56. OR'
b'Recommendation Letters:'
b'3 required'
